President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Georgia due to Hurricane Irma and has ordered Federal aid to assist in recovery efforts. The declaration makes Federal funding available to affected individuals in the counties of Camden, Chatham, and Glynn. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid individuals and business owners in recovering from the disaster. Federal funding is also available for emergency work and hazard mitigation measures in all 159 counties of the State. Thomas J. McCool has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing in other areas, and additional counties may be designated for assistance in the future. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by calling the provided toll-free numbers. For further information, media should contact the FEMA News Desk.